In [4]:
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

n_neighbors = range(1, 30)
train_accuracy = []
test_accuracy = []
print ("K-Nearest Neighbors accuracy score")
for n in n_neighbors:
    neigh = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=n)
    neigh.fit(train_data, train_label)
    
    pred = neigh.predict(train_data)
    train_accuracy.append(accuracy_score(train_label, pred))
    
    pred = neigh.predict(test_data)
    test_accuracy.append(accuracy_score(test_label, pred))
    
    print ("\tFor n_neighbors =", n, "train:", train_accuracy[-1], "test:", test_accuracy[-1])

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

cluster_counts = [10]
accuracy = []
def create_k_means(data, cluster_count):
    km = KMeans(n_clusters=cluster_count)
    km.fit(data)
    
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(cluster_count//2, 2, figsize=(14, 14))
    fig.tight_layout()
    fig.suptitle("K-Means for cluster_count: {}".format(cluster_count))
    for i, center in enumerate(km.cluster_centers_):
        img = Image.new('L', (28, 28))
        img.putdata(center)
        axs[i//2, i%2].set_title('Cluster {}'.format(i))
        axs[i//2, i%2].imshow(img)
        
    return km

km = create_k_means(train_data, cluster_count=cluster_counts[-1])

import numpy as np

def k_means_accuracy_score(k_means, data, labels, cluster_count):
    cluster_answers = [[0 for j in range(10)] for i in range(cluster_count)]
    
    for i, data in data.iterrows():
        predict_me = np.array(data)
        predict_me = predict_me.reshape(-1, len(predict_me))
        prediction = k_means.predict(predict_me)
        
        answer_index = labels.iloc[i]
        cluster_answers[prediction[0]][answer_index] += 1
        
    print_cluster_answers(cluster_answers)

    correct_answer = sum(map(max, cluster_answers))
    return correct_answer / len(test_data)

def print_cluster_answers(cluster_answers):
    correct_answers = list(map(max, cluster_answers))
    print("\tcluster mapping:")
    for i, cluster_answer in enumerate(cluster_answers):
        correct_number = cluster_answer.index(correct_answers[i]) 
        print("\t\tcluster", i, "-> number:", correct_number)
    

print("K-Means accuracy score")
accuracy.append(k_means_accuracy_score(km, test_data, test_label, cluster_count=cluster_counts[-1]))
print("\tcluster_count:", 10, "accuracy:", accuracy[-1])

def plot_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, classes, normalize=False, title=None, cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
    """
    This function prints and plots the confusion matrix.
    Normalization can be applied by setting `normalize=True`.
    """
    # Compute confusion matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)

    if normalize:
        cm = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 8))
    im = ax.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    ax.figure.colorbar(im, ax=ax)
    # We want to show all ticks...
    ax.set(xticks=np.arange(cm.shape[1]),
           yticks=np.arange(cm.shape[0]),
           # ... and label them with the respective list entries
           xticklabels=classes, yticklabels=classes,
           title=title,
           ylabel='True label',
           xlabel='Predicted label')

    # Rotate the tick labels and set their alignment.
    plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right", rotation_mode="anchor")

    # Loop over data dimensions and create text annotations.
    fmt = '.2f' if normalize else 'd'
    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i in range(cm.shape[0]):
        for j in range(cm.shape[1]):
            ax.text(j, i, format(cm[i, j], fmt),
                    ha="center", va="center",
                    color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")
    fig.tight_layout()
    return ax

class_names = range(0, 9)

# Plot non-normalized confusion matrix
plot_confusion_matrix(test_label, pred, classes=class_names, title='Confusion matrix, without normalization')

# Plot normalized confusion matrix
plot_confusion_matrix(test_label, pred, classes=class_names, normalize=True, title='Normalized confusion matrix')

plt.show()

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

pca = PCA(n_components=20)
principal_train_components = pca.fit_transform(train_data)
principal_test_components = pca.transform(test_data)

neigh = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=12)
neigh.fit(principal_train_components, train_label)

pred = neigh.predict(principal_train_components)
train_accuracy = accuracy_score(train_label, pred)

pred = neigh.predict(principal_test_components)
test_accuracy = accuracy_score(test_label, pred)

print ("K-Nearest Neighbors accuracy score for PCA data")
print ("\tFor n_neighbors =", 12, "train:", train_accuracy, "test:", test_accuracy)

K-Nearest Neighbors accuracy score for PCA data
	For n_neighbors = 12 train: 0.934 test: 0.93
